1069
Your Honor,

I, Aleksander Nowak, stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of assault. I regretfully admit that I engaged in physical violence towards my employee, pushing him to the ground and subsequently kicking him in the stomach.

While I fully acknowledge the severity of my actions, I do want to provide some context for the court's consideration. My employee's serious mistake at work caused significant financial consequences for my company, resulting in heightened emotions on my part. However, I understand that resorting to physical violence was entirely inappropriate and unjustifiable.

Immediately following the incident, I was overwhelmed with remorse for my impulsive and aggressive behavior. Recognizing the harm inflicted on my employee, I quickly sought to rectify the situation by bringing him to the nearest emergency room to ensure his well-being. Additionally, I have personally expressed my sincerest apologies to both the victim and his family for the inexcusable conduct on my part.

I accept full responsibility for the harm and distress caused by my actions. As an act of accountability, I have already offered to cover all expenses related to my employee's remaining hospital bills.

I must emphasize that this incident is an outlier in my otherwise law-abiding life. At 40 years old, I do not have any prior criminal record, which further demonstrates the uncharacteristic nature of my behavior.

Through this statement, I express my understanding of the gravity of my actions and my unwavering commitment to accepting the consequences associated with my guilty plea. I am genuinely remorseful and fully committed to learning from this experience and ensuring that such behavior never repeats itself.

As I move forward, I am dedicated to seeking appropriate help and support to address any underlying issues that may have contributed to my improper reaction.

Your Honor, I humbly request your understanding and leniency as I take responsibility for my offense. I acknowledge the harm caused and the necessity of appropriate repercussions. I respectfully submit myself to the judgment of this court, with the hope that the mitigating factors present in my case will be considered.

I appreciate Your Honor's attention and consideration.

Thank you.
