982
Your Honor,

I, Aleksander Nowak, humbly stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of assault. I regretfully admit that I engaged in physical violence towards my employee, pushing him to the ground and subsequently kicking him in the stomach.

Immediately after the incident occurred, I was overwhelmed with remorse for my impulsive and aggressive behavior. I swiftly recognized the harm inflicted on my employee and promptly brought him to the nearest emergency room to ensure his well-being. I express my sincerest apologies to both the victim and his family for the inexcusable conduct on my part.

I understand the gravity of my actions and fully accept responsibility for the consequences associated with my guilty plea. This incident is a stark departure from my otherwise law-abiding life, as I am 40 years old and have no prior criminal record. I assure this honorable court that my actions on that fateful day do not reflect my true character.

While it is true that my employee's serious mistake at work caused significant financial consequences for my company, leading to heightened emotions on my part, I now realize that resorting to physical violence was both inappropriate and unjustifiable. I now understand that there are appropriate ways to address issues in the workplace, and I am committed to ensuring that such behavior never repeats itself.

Through this statement, I express my heartfelt remorse and commit to learning from this experience. I have already offered to pay for the rest of my employee's hospital bills as a tangible expression of my remorse and willingness to make amends.

Your Honor, I humbly request your understanding and leniency as I take full responsibility for my offense. I respectfully submit myself to the judgment of this court, confident that the mitigating factors present in my case will be considered.

Thank you for your attention and consideration.

Sincerely,
Aleksander Nowak
