Your Honor,

I, Aleksander Nowak, stand before you today to plea guilty to the charge of assault. I am deeply remorseful for the incident where I pushed my employee to the ground and proceeded to kick him in the stomach.

In the aftermath of this grave mistake, I was overwhelmed with regret for my impulsive and aggressive behavior. Realizing the harm I had inflicted, my immediate response was to take my employee to the nearest emergency room in order to ensure his well-being. I extend my sincerest apologies to the victim and his family for the inexcusable conduct on my part.

I am fully aware of the seriousness of my actions and accept accountability for the consequences resulting from my guilty plea. I humbly request the court to take into consideration that this incident does not reflect my character. At 40 years of age, I have maintained an untarnished and reputable record throughout my life.

While it is true that my employee's substantial mistake at work resulted in financial losses for my company, I have come to understand that resorting to physical violence was entirely inappropriate and unjustifiable. I have since learned that there are more constructive methods to address workplace issues, and I am strongly committed to ensuring that such behavior never occurs again.

To make amends, I express my deepest remorse and have already offered to cover the remaining hospital bills for my employee. This action serves as evidence of my genuine commitment to accepting responsibility for my actions and making appropriate restitution.

Your Honor, I humbly request your understanding and leniency as I fully acknowledge the gravity of my offense. I have learned a valuable lesson from this experience and am determined to grow as an individual.

Thank you for your attention and kind consideration.

Respectfully,

Aleksander Nowak
